         <div type="translation" resp="part:vito">
             <p>The Bhagavant, Perfectly and Completely Awakened One Sighi (Skt. Śikhin): commissioned by the <foreign>upāsaka</foreign> Visāgha (Skt. Viśākha) of the Vāgāḍhica family, together with his son<supplied reason="subaudible">s</supplied>. Made by Nāgabuddhi, the son of Māḍha, grandson of Sāmināga, and great-grandson of Āsadeva, the sculptor.</p>
         </div>
